
MISDA PROJECT FILE STRUCTURE
================================================================================

1. CORE LIBRARY
----------------

misda.py

    The main library file containing the implementation of the MISDA algorithm
    (analyze, reduce, compile_benchmark_summary), diagnostic metrics
    (calculate_ses, calculate_ses_nonlinear), and helper classes.

mop_definitions.py

    Helper module containing definitions for synthetic MOP generators used in
    tests, though some are also embedded directly in notebooks.


2. NOTEBOOKS & BENCHMARKS (User-Facing)
----------------------------------------

benchmark.ipynb

    The primary test suite covering:
      - 7 Canonical Cases (structural logic tests: Independence, Redundancy...)
      - 6 Synthetic MOPs (A-F) testing complex correlations, non-linearity,
        and regime switching.


dtlz.ipynb

    Specialized benchmark for geometric manifolds (DTLZ2, DTLZ5) and high-
    dimensional analysis (M=10), featuring 3D reconstruction visualizations.

ISDA_1_0.ipynb

    Legacy or reference notebook for previous versions (if applicable).


3. PROJECT METADATA & SETUP
----------------------------

pyproject.toml
    Modern build configuration file (PEP 612). Defines project metadata,
    dependencies (numpy, pandas, scipy, networkx, matplotlib, sklearn),
    and build system requirements (setuptools). Replaces setup.py.

README.md

    Project overview, installation instructions, and quick start guide.

CONTRIBUTING.md

    Guidelines for external contributors.

CHANGELOG.md

    History of version updates and fixes (e.g., transition to v0.2.0).

AUTHORS

    List of project authors/maintainers.

LICENSE

    The primary license file for the project.

LICENSES/

    Directory containing full text of applicable licenses (e.g., GPL-3.0).

REUSE.toml

    Configuration for REUSE compliance (license tracking).


4. TESTING & VERIFICATION SCRIPTS (Dev)
----------------------------------------

verify_example.py

    A minimal script to sanity-check the basic misda.analyze functionality.

verify_table.py

    Script used to verify the output formatting of summary tables.

verify_mop.py

    Dedicated script for verifying MOP generator logic.

run_summary_test.py

    Utility to test the compile_benchmark_summary function specifically.
